# Migration Framework with YAML-Based Registration

Absolutely! We can simplify the migration framework by using YAML files for registration. This approach combines the clean architecture of our initial design with a more declarative way to register migrations.

Here's how we can adapt the design:

## 1. YAML Migration Manifest

Instead of manually registering migrations in code, we'll define them in YAML files:

```yaml
# migrations/manifests/delete_old_documents.yaml
id: "delete-old-documents"
version: "1.0.0"
description: "Delete documents older than 1 year"
implementation: "DeleteOldDocumentsMigration"
```

## 2. Migration Implementation

The migration implementation will be similar to our initial design, but without the registration code:

```go
